In a bid to extend high-quality services to German and Nigerian companies and to promote newer investment partnerships, the Delegation of German Industry and Commerce in Nigeria (AHK Nigeria) will be hosting the West African Clean Energy and Environment (WACEE) trade fair and conference in Lagos. The hybrid event themed: ‘Catalysing Sustainable Investments’ is scheduled to be held from October 19 to 21 at the Landmark Event Centre. Speaking ahead of the conference, AHK Nigeria Delegate, Katharina Felgenhauer said this year’s edition is unique as it marks the 10th anniversary of WACEE. “In the past decade, the West African Clean Energy and Environment Trade Fair and Conference has evolved into the subregion’s leading event focusing on clean energy, water and the circular economy. The trade fair and conference has attracted leading inventors, service providers, manufacturers, suppliers and distributors, i nvestors and industry experts and has served as a gateway for these stakeholders to access West African markets,” she said. According to Felgenhauer, two-country pavilions: the German Pavilion supported by the Association of the German Trade Fair Industry (AUMA) and the Austrian Pavilion organised by the Austrian Embassy Commercial Section are already confirmed to be at the 3-day conference On his part, the Acting Consul General for Germany in Lagos, Marton Köver expressed optimism about the business potential of the Nigerian market. The German government has lamented the consequences of climate change in the world Acting Consul General of the country s mission in Lagos Marton Kover said tackling climate change and doing everything to mitigate its consequences is a top priority Kover stated this at a press conference in Lagos organized by the German Industry and Trade hellip Having been held virtually in 2020, due to the coronavirus pandemic, this year WACEE would provide a platform for more than 1,500 visitors and more than 50 exhibitors in the clean energy, water and circular economy sectors. According to the organisers, having an event that brings together saving the planet, strengthening the economy and creating economic ties is like having the best of both worlds. They further called on Nigerian companies and all who are interested in these different sectors; circular economy, water and renewable energies, to participate in the event, especially since Nigeria has for many decades been one of Germany’s economic partners in Africa, as evidenced by the number of German companies and historical ties.